AGI - After the Palestinian government, Hamas also condemned the military operations carried out by Israel in the occupied West Bank. For the Palestinian armed group, Israel's decision to expand its operations in the Jenin governorate and in other parts of the north of the occupied West Bank reveals its "dangerous intention to persist in the extermination war". In a statement Hamas also asks to create a "united front" against "the forced displacement campaigns of Israel" which hit more than 40,000 residents of the refugee camps of Jenin, Tulkarem, Nur Shams and Far'a.
The Palestinian armed group has also rejected a statement of the Israeli defence minister, Israel Katz - who has asserted that the Israeli army will remain in the refugee camps of the West Bank for the next year - defining it "an illusion that will not happen".
For the Palestinian Foreign Ministry, the deployment of Israeli tanks in the West Bank represents "a serious escalation". The sentence comes in a statement posted on X, in which the ministry affirmed that the deployment of tanks in the occupied West Bank is a continuation of the "genocide, displacement and annexation" of Israel. The tanks, along with the forced displacement of 40,000 Palestinians and the statement of Israeli Defense Minister Israel Katz that Palestinians cannot return to their homes, represent a "grave escalation".
"The Ministry renews its urgent appeal to the international community to intervene immediately to stop the uncontrolled aggression of Israel," he added. Israeli tanks were deployed yesterday in the occupied West Bank for the first time in more than 20 years, while 40,000 Palestinians fled the Israeli assault on the refugee camps in the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<h2>Tregua and hostages
Despite the tensions of the last few hours, Israel is confident that Hamas will allow to release other hostages in the current phase of the truce agreement. To write it is the Jerusalem Post. The idea, already circulated in recent days, is that the first phase continues over the 42 days planned.
According to the sources quoted by the daily newspaper, the extension would lead to the release of four men and other seriously injured persons, in exchange for the extension of the ceasefire during Ramadan. The sacred month of Islam will begin on the night between Friday and Saturday, when phase 1 of the understanding should expire.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
The White House, in the meantime, declared to support Israel's decision to delay the release of 600 Palestinian prisoners.' The Times of Israel newspaper reports it. "With the barbaric treatment of the hostages by Hamas, including the horrific parade of the children's coffins of the Bibas family on the streets of Gaza, Israel's decision to delay the release of prisoners is an appropriate response," said a statement by the spokesman of the National Security Council, Brian Hughes. "The President is ready to support Israel in any action line chooses against Hamas," he adds.
&nbsp;
